text: Michael G. Weist III (born 25 July 1996) is an American producer and actor. He is known for his role as an actor in the Hulu movie Jawline, which won the 2019 Sundance Film Festival. Weist is a member of the Recording Academy. Weist's television and movie work includes guest appearances on Dr. Phil, The Kids Choice Awards, The Grammy's, and appearances in movies. Weist stars in the Amazon Prime Original, TanaCon: What Really Happened, Shane Dawson's The Truth About TanaCon, and more. In June 2018, Weist held an event in collaboration with youtuber Tana Mongeau; called "TanaCon." The event was cancelled just hours after it began. == References == Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:American movie actors Category:American producers
